(30, '<br>Key Area 2 <br>Key Area 3 ', 'Atmospheric Physics<br>Stellar Occultations<br>Public Outreach / Education etc<br>Orbital Mechanics<br><br>Comments:<br>a. In 2007 we contributed with an  observation of a mutual event between the Uranian satellites Umbriel and Oberon. Paper published in A&amp;A: http://www.aanda.org/index.php?option=article&amp;access=doi&amp;doi=10.1051/0004-6361/200811523    b. In 2009 and 2010 we made many successfull observations of Saturnian and Jovian mutual events for PHEMU09 and PHESAT-09, which we have submitted to IMCCE (FR).    3. In August 3rd 2009 we have made a successfull observation of the occultation of 45-Capricorni by Jupiter see: http://www.iota-es.de/jupiter2009/occultation_results01.html  Our preliminary light curves: http://www.spartastronomy.gr/arthra/jupiter_45_cap/light-curves     4. Asteroid astrometry and asteroidal occultaions are other areas of interest for Ellinogermaniki Agogi Observatory.  ', 'a. In 2007 we contributed with an  observation of a mutual event between the Uranian satellites Umbriel and Oberon. Paper published in A&amp;A: http://www.aanda.org/index.php?option=article&amp;access=doi&amp;doi=10.1051/0004-6361/200811523    b. In 2009 and 2010 we made many successfull observations of Saturnian and Jovian mutual events for PHEMU09 and PHESAT-09, which we have submitted to IMCCE (FR).    3. In August 3rd 2009 we have made a successfull observation of the occultation of 45-Capricorni by Jupiter see: http://www.iota-es.de/jupiter2009/occultation_results01.html  Our preliminary light curves: http://www.spartastronomy.gr/arthra/jupiter_45_cap/light-curves     4. Asteroid astrometry and asteroidal occultaions are other areas of interest for Ellinogermaniki Agogi Observatory.  ', 30),
