(123, 'The following core instruments are available at the Nordic Optical Telescope:    FIES: http://www.not.iac.es/instruments/fies/  FIES is a cross-dispersed high-resolution echelle spectrograph with a maximum spectral resolution of R = 67000. The entire spectral range 370-730 nm is covered without gaps in a single, fixed setting. For bright stars, a radial velocity precision of order 5 m/s is obtained.    ALFOSC: http://www.not.iac.es/instruments/alfosc/  ALFOSC has a field of view of 6.4x6.4 arcminutes in imaging mode, and can also be used for low/medium resolution spectroscopy, and polarimetry.     NOTCAM: http://www.not.iac.es/instruments/notcam/  NOTCam is a multi-mode instrument for use in the short-wave infrared (SWIR). Capabilities:  Wide field imaging (4''?4'' @ 0.234&quot;/pixel)  High resolution imaging (80&quot;?80&quot; @ 0.078&quot;/pixel)  Low-res (R = 2500) WF-cam spectroscopy (Y,J,H,K)  Medium-res (R = 5500) HR-cam spectroscopy (J,H,K)', '', '', '', 123),
